1.2.21
- Bags BiS: fix Adventurer's Tattered Sack linked ownership. Rank suffixes in
  parentheses are no longer stripped during name match (that collapsed every
  rank to the base name). Runtime expander adds higher-rank IDs/names like
  fungal; Frame/materials clear from the matching sack rank (Frame at Celestial).
  Also normalizes backtick/curly apostrophes in item names.

1.2.20
- Bags BiS: Adventurer's Tattered Sack ranks (151053-151057) chain like fungal /
  Jonas - owning a higher sack clears lower ranks. Reinforced Stitching Frame
  (151058) stays needed until Celestial (151057), then Frame + lower sacks show
  owned. Bag multi-ID ownership chains are honored again (no longer stripped).
- Vendor BiS (CLR PAL RNG SHD DRU SHM NEC WIZ MAG ENC BST): Discordian adds
  Volatile Discordian Rune (150040), Focus Shard of Destruction (150047) and
  Focus Shard of Atrophy (150048) with hover notes that they are weaker than
  typed augs but cover all spell/DoT types; Planar adds Volatile Planar Rune
  (150033).
- Rule pack: Epic Quest Items Mega (ANNOUNCE) for class epic quest items;
  sits beside the smaller epic_quests KEEP pack.

1.2.19
- Characters pill (four modes) pinned under main tabs when relevant:
  Roster (Source / columns / teams) on BiS, Spells, Lockouts, and Stats Search;
  Primary (Source + one character) on Upgrade Suggestions and Gear Inventory
  (Source drives Slot Across Characters; Character drives the inventory view);
  Picker (flat character list) on Worn / Stored, Inspect Effects / Focus /
  Stats Character, Upgrade Empty, and Compare Worn / Char 1; List (loadout
  picker) on Stats Plan in the same pill slot. Legacy who-controls hide when
  the pill is on (Settings.showCharactersPill, default on). Pill uses muted-teal
  chrome. Gear Inventory: Slot Across Characters moves above the worn/item
  layout, collapses, and sizes to the character row count. Main + secondary tabs
  (Gear/Inspect/Upgrade/BiS) stay pinned above the scroll body. Search Everywhere
  is a search mode: results only until cleared. Gear multi Group/E3 modes remain
  when the pill is off.
- Suggestions segments renamed Gear upgrades / Empty sockets (N) / Socket plan.
  Gear is home with collapsible Empty/Plan teasers; Empty sockets quiet when 0
  (diagnostics under Why?); Socket plan quiet when no positive net gains (funnel
  under Why?); Top Actions only lists gain moves.
- Inspect Stats: Character / Plan / Search stay pinned above the scroll body
  (with Stats / Effects / Focus). Worn totals header uses higher-contrast text.
- Review right-click: Go loot (same TurboLoot GO path as linked-needs). Sends
  the skip source character when remote, else Me. Needs a corpse id; local Me
  also aborts on zone mismatch. Does not prove the item is still on the corpse.
  On TurboLoot `[GOLOOT] looted` (or TurboGear relay), the skip row is dismissed
  from Review automatically; failed go-loot leaves the row for retry. Routes via
  `/tgearbg` when the bg responder is up, else `/tgear` (UI), else local
  `/mac TurboLoot go`. Does not call `mq.doevents` in the hub loop (that broke
  TurboLoot GO). Go loot is a submenu: pick any group member (Src first, then
  you, then the rest) — not limited to the designated looter.

1.2.18
- DoN / Dragons of Norrath Raid BiS tab: LazBiS `don` list + catalog regen, UI
  button, TurboLoot BiS_announce_list names. Spell packs clear when the pack is
  owned or all pack spells/discs are known; Mnemonic/Imbued Glyphs stay item-only.
  Refinements: Ranged+Aug pairs, Icon clickies, Shadow/Materium chain, Cryptic
  Clutch short labels linked to Vacant Vessel IDs, foci hover notes. Misc4 Scales
  of the Lava Dragon also clears when the class Draconic epic is owned. Category
  order: Spells → Glyphs → Foci → Clickies → Shadow → Misc.
- Linked-needs: guild and OOC item-link listening off by default; Setup toggles
  to enable either without changing group/raid/say behavior.
- BiS hover: slimmed (name + notes + location); foci notes use ASCII dashes;
  melee / defense / heal-beneficial note colors added.

1.2.17
- Go loot: item name was the literal string NULL — `BuildGoItemName` ran as a
  Sub so `${Param2}` was that Sub's empty args (MQ NULL), not Main's `/mac`
  words. Join Param2.. in Sub Main before any `/call`.

1.2.16
- Go loot: MQ was dropping multi-word item names when passed as a Sub string
  arg (`[GOLOOT] starting (ID: n)` with no name → false not_found / "item gone").
  GO mode now keeps the name in outer `goItemName` only.

1.2.15
- Go loot: hand the excursion to TurboLoot (`/mac TurboLoot go <corpseId> <Item>`).
  TurboGear only dispatches and reports panel status from `/tgearbg golootdone`
  (looted / failed reasons / going). Fixes Lua vs mac timing races that left
  characters stuck on reveal or an open loot window.

1.2.14
- Go loot: wait for Corpse.Items to populate after LootWnd opens (TurboLoot does);
  find loot slots via Corpse.Item[=name]/partial/id; retry itemnotify with and
  without /ctrl; mash no-drop confirm while picking up so we do not sit on an
  open corpse inventory.

1.2.13
- Go loot: panel no longer regresses opening/looting back to "going"; /loot fires
  immediately on open; lootnodrop always for the pickup; dual yes-button confirm;
  stronger E3 pause so reveal is not fighting a still-live E3 for several seconds.

1.2.12
- Go loot: trust TurboLoot corpse spawn ids regardless of Type; longer reveal
  with pulses/target nudges; if Spawn TLO stays empty, blind /nav id then open;
  faster runner loop + immediate tick pump so reveal does not stall after ack.

1.2.11
- Go loot: if already in range, skip /nav and open immediately (fixes 8ft "nav
  reached later, never looted"); retarget/face + /loot retries; loot-anyway when
  target will not stick; job watchdog resumes E3; duplicate Go acks "going"
  instead of leaving the panel on "sent"; phase notes (revealing/heading/...).

1.2.10
- Go loot: pause E3 (/e3p on) for the run like TurboLoot so chase/follow cannot
  cancel nav after Reloot; longer corpse reveal wait + retries; re-issue nav
  while walking if interrupted.

1.2.9
- Go loot: duplicate Go clicks / double actor delivery no longer report "busy"
  while the same corpse job is already revealing or navigating; ack "going" on
  accept so the panel does not stick on a false busy from the duplicate.

1.2.8
- Go loot: if the corpse spawn is not visible (common after TurboLoot hidecorpse),
  unhide with /hidecorpse none like Reloot, wait briefly, retry once, then nav/loot;
  restore /hidecorpse looted when the job ends so the world is not left cluttered.

1.2.7
- Hotfix: Clear-all helper is stored on TG instead of a chunk local so Turbo
  init.lua stays under LuaJIT's 200-local main-function limit (load failure on
  /lua run turbo after 1.2.6).

1.2.6
- Linked items: show corpse spawn ID in its own column next to Age so you can
  call out which NPC corpse still has the item (same id TurboLoot prints on
  [ANNOUNCE]/[SKIP] lines).
- Go loot: on success, urgently republish the looter's inventory and request a
  fast snap on the driver (same path as need-confirm), flushing the shared cache
  so BiS / needs_index reflect ownership without waiting for the ~30s bg save.
- Review: Clear all skips loads each turboloot.ini [ItemLimits] once (section
  lookup) instead of N per-item INI reads — same expected-skip filter and
  mark_ts revive semantics, without the UI hitch on large pending lists.

1.2.5
- Go loot: announce-passive bg on the driver box now relays peer LOOT_LINK /
  lootseen drops to the local UI via /tgear lootseenquiet. Actors only land on
  the bg mailbox, so 1.2.4's corpse-aware broadcast never reached the panel that
  draws Go buttons (plain red needers). Also treat a missing corpse_at as fresh
  when corpse_id is present, and tooltip Age/needers when Go is unavailable.

1.2.4
- Go loot / announce: TurboLoot's structured handoff now calls /tgearbg (looters
  usually bind that, not /tgear) and passes the corpse spawn id, then broadcasts
  it to peer drivers over actors so the Linked items panel can show Go buttons
  even when other-player chat links do not parse. ANNOUNCE/SKIP chat parsing is
  tougher about link frames, and a pending linked row appears as soon as a
  corpse id and needers are known (before the [TG] flush).

1.2.3
- Go loot: pause /afollow and stop /chaseme before walking to the corpse, then
  /afollow unpause on finish - same prelude as TurboLoot sell/bank/tribute so
  followers resume chase correctly instead of fighting nav or standing at the
  corpse.
- TurboLoot: [ANNOUNCE]/[SKIP] dedupe buffer raised (~40 keys -> ~200) so a
  mid-pull wipe no longer double-announces items still on corpses; corpse (ID:)
  stamps prefer the loot-loop corpse id over Target.ID so Go buttons cannot
  point at the wrong corpse when target drifts.
- Announce: also capture guild and OOC item links (group/raid/say already
  worked). [TG] need-lines are still skipped so we never re-announce needs.
- Needs index warm-up: the bg responder now builds peer needs even while
  announce-passive (its direct catalogs persist to disk for the UI driver);
  the queue is pruned to the announce roster; lean/minimized UIs temporarily
  raise their index budget when the oldest queued rebuild is older than 60s.

1.2.2
- Go loot: the BiS tab's linked-items panel now shows a Go button per needer
  when TurboLoot left the item on a corpse (ANNOUNCE/SKIP rules). Clicking it
  sends that character to the corpse over the actor bus: they nav (or moveto)
  there, open the corpse, pick up exactly that item, and report the outcome
  back into the panel (looted / corpse gone / item gone / couldn't reach).
  Guards: same-zone only, distance cap, combat check, corpse-age timeout, and
  one run at a time per character. Buttons hide once the corpse hint is stale.

1.2.1
- Updates: the patch-lock stop now covers the whole suite. The Turbo hub watches
  for the patcher's lock file itself (and ends any running macro), and TurboGear
  stops the hub along with the other Turbo scripts, so clicking Update while
  everything is running cleanly shuts it all down on every box.
- One version number everywhere: the Turbo hub window now shows the suite
  version from this CHANGELOG (the same number TurboPatcher displays) instead
  of its old internal 3.9.x script version.
- New /turbopatcher command launches TurboPatcher.exe while Turbo is already
  running (the /lua run Turbo patcher form only works when Turbo is stopped,
  since MQ refuses to start a script that is already loaded).
- Releases: the Linux zip is now built and attached automatically when a
  release is published on GitHub, so it always matches the released source.

1.2.0
- Announce: linked items now resolve by name before parsed-link id, so shared
  id ranges (for example the Jonas Dagmire hand bones) can no longer credit the
  wrong bone; alias pairs like "Triquetrum" and "Jonas Dagmire's Triquetrum"
  collapse to a single announce instead of two.
- Announce: cache-derived peer needers are live-confirmed over the actor bus
  before a grouped [TG] send, so characters who already looted the item are
  dropped from the needer list instead of being announced stale.
- Updates: Turbo scripts stop themselves when TurboPatcher starts an update
  (patch-lock hook), and the More tab gained a Turbo Patcher button that
  launches the patcher directly (drop TurboPatcher.exe in your MacroQuest
  folder so the button can find it).
- ResearchLearn spell-research automation moved out of the suite to become a
  separate project. TurboGear's Spells tab still tracks missing research
  spells and exports per-character want lists.

1.1.0
- SQLite storage is now the default (storeBackend = "auto"): the SQLite backend
  is used automatically when lsqlite3 is available, and lsqlite3 is auto-installed
  from the MacroQuest LuaRocks server on first use via mq/PackageMan (like LazBis).
  Falls back to the file cache if lsqlite3 cannot be installed or loaded.
- Added `/tgear backend auto|file|sqlite` and a Setup-tab "Storage" toggle to
  switch backends without editing files (applies on restart).

1.0.0
- Storage: new SQLite backend (WAL) behind a pluggable store backend interface;
  concurrent multi-box writes with no clobber race, change-detected upserts, and
  a one-time import of the legacy pickle cache. Ships dormant (storeBackend =
  "file"); set storeBackend = "auto" after an in-game smoke test to enable it.
  Falls back to the file cache automatically when lsqlite3 is unavailable.
- Sync: cross-box update ordering now uses a per-publisher monotonic sequence
  instead of wall-clock timestamps, so clock skew between boxes can no longer
  drop a fresh update or accept a stale one. Wire-compatible (no proto bump).
- Startup: the viewer waits for the background responder's readiness ack before
  delegating its first sync (with a deadline fallback), instead of a fixed
  /timed delay that could fire before the responder's mailbox was live.
- Performance: background BiS catalog (~34k lines) is now lazy-loaded on first
  use; the per-source online/stale/offline aging sweep is throttled to ~1Hz;
  announce catalog-warm + needs-index work draws down from a single per-frame
  budget; the file cache no longer re-reads/merges the whole file when this box
  is the sole writer, and re-validates the temp file only periodically.
- Reliability/observability: swallowed actor-send/file errors are now recorded
  and surfaced in /tgear perfdiag; memo-cache sizes are bounded and reported;
  perfdiag gained per-frame work-time, Lua heap, and catalog-residency gauges.
- Testing: full offline suite (15 files) runs under LuaJIT 2.1 (MacroQuest's
  runtime) via a CI-style runner (lua/tests/run_all.lua), including a real
  SQLite engine exercised through an lsqlite3 FFI shim. Graceful-degradation
  fallbacks (no actors, no lsqlite3, missing cache) are covered by tests.
- Docs: added lua/turbogear/README.md (architecture, storage backends, perfdiag).

0.2.1
- Prior baseline (pre-hardening): live multi-character inventory/BiS/announce
  engine on the MQ actor bus with a single atomic Lua-pickle cache.
